It can cause the kidneys to fail (end-stage renal disease, or ESRD) forcing a patient to start dialysis or receive a kidney transplant. In endemic areas BEN is responsible for up to 70% of ESRD. At least 25,000 individuals are known to have the disease.<ref>The Epidemiology, Diagnosis, and Management of Aristolochic Acid Nephropathy: A Narrative Review [http://annals.org/article.aspx?articleid=1667269 Annals of Internal Medicine] 19 March 2013, Vol 158, No. 6</ref>-->

症狀包括虛弱，貧血，及銅色皮膚變色。
